   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>TO THE READER.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">E</seg>Nough, if not too much, hath been sayd of this Translation. If the faults found euen by my selfe in the first impression, be now by the Printer corre<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>cted, as he was directed, the worke is much amen<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ded: If not, know, that through mine attendance on hir Maiestie, I could not intend-it; and blame not <hi>Neptune</hi> for thy second shipwracke. Let me conclude with this worthie mans daughter of alliance: <hi>Que t'en semble donc lecteur?</hi>
   </p>
   <closer>
      <signed>Still resolute IOHN FLORIO.</signed>
   </closer>
